   {:e #blake3 "60a67c60c7f3ee1381924a6143a19508fc6eb6814d6a2ac4d8ef5c815bf53c30" :a :db/doc :v "Self-Bootstrap Fixed-Point Property" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "60a67c60c7f3ee1381924a6143a19508fc6eb6814d6a2ac4d8ef5c815bf53c30" :a :spec/source-file :v "00-preamble.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "60a67c60c7f3ee1381924a6143a19508fc6eb6814d6a2ac4d8ef5c815bf53c30" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §10, C7, ADRS LM-008\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Problem\nDDIS specifies itself (C7). What does self-bootstrap convergence look like, and how do\nwe know when it has been achieved?\n\n#### Options\nA) **Spec as external document only** — The specification is a document that describes\n   the system. The system manages other data, not its own spec. No self-reference.\nB) **Spec as data, convergence by fiat** — The specification is loaded into the datom\n   store, but convergence is declared rather than verified. The spec-as-document and\n   spec-as-data may silently diverge.\nC) **Spec as data with fixed-point convergence** — The specification is both a document\n   and data in the store. Convergence is achieved when the specification-as-data and the\n   specification-as-document agree. The specification process itself generates the first\n   test data: invariants about the store become the store's test cases; contradictions\n   caught during specification become contradiction-detection test cases.\n\n#### Decision\n**Option C.** When the system manages its own specification, the specification IS data.\nThe self-bootstrap fixed-point is reached when:\n1. Every specification element exists as a datom in the store\n2. The datom representation is faithful (no lossy transformation)\n3. The system can verify its own specification for internal contradictions\n4. The specification process generates test cases for the system's verification machinery\n\n#### Formal Justification\nLet `spec_doc` be the specification as a document and `spec_data` be the specification as\ndatoms in the store. The fixed-point condition is:\n```\nparse(spec_doc) = spec_data   AND   render(spec_data) = spec_doc\n```\nThis is a round-trip property: parse and render are inverses. At the fixed point, there is\none specification with two representations (document and datoms) that agree exactly.\n\nThe specification process is self-validating: writing INV-STORE-001 (append-only) as a\ndatom tests whether the store can represent its own invariants. If the store cannot\nrepresent INV-STORE-001, the invariant and the store are inconsistent — which is exactly\nthe kind of divergence DDIS is designed to detect.\n\n#### Consequences\n- The first act of Stage 0 is migrating specification elements into the datom store\n- The migration is a test: if it fails, the spec-element schema is incomplete\n- Round-trip fidelity (parse -> datom -> render -> document) is a verification target\n- The contradiction detection engine's first test case is the specification itself\n- Self-bootstrap is not a one-time event but an ongoing fixed-point maintenance\n\n#### Falsification\nThis decision is wrong if: the specification cannot be faithfully represented as datoms\n(some element type or relationship has no datom encoding), making the round-trip property\nimpossible to achieve.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "60a67c60c7f3ee1381924a6143a19508fc6eb6814d6a2ac4d8ef5c815bf53c30" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §10, C7, ADRS LM-008" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "60a67c60c7f3ee1381924a6143a19508fc6eb6814d6a2ac4d8ef5c815bf53c30" :a :adr/problem :v "DDIS specifies itself (C7). What does self-bootstrap convergence look like, and how do we know when it has been achieved?" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "60a67c60c7f3ee1381924a6143a19508fc6eb6814d6a2ac4d8ef5c815bf53c30" :a :adr/decision :v "**Option C.** When the system manages its own specification, the specification IS data. The self-bootstrap fixed-point is reached when: 1. Every specification element exists as a datom in the store 2. The datom representation is faithful (no lossy transformation) 3. The system can verify its own specification for internal contradictions 4. The specification process generates test cases for the system's verification machinery" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-001 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :db/doc :v "Append-Only Immutability" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4 Axiom 2, C1, ADRS FD-001\n**Verification**: `V:TYPE`, `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ S ∈ Store, S' = TRANSACT(S, T) for any T:\n  S ⊆ S'\n  (monotonicity: once asserted, never lost)\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nFor all reachable states (S, S') where S →[op] S':\n  `S.datoms ⊆ S'.datoms`\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n#[kani::ensures(|result| old(store.datoms.len()) <= store.datoms.len())]\nfn transact(store: &mut Store, tx: Transaction<Committed>) -> Result<TxReceipt, TxApplyError>;\n```\n\n**Falsification**: Any operation that reduces `store.datoms.len()` or removes a\npreviously-observed datom from the set.\n\n**proptest strategy**: Generate random sequences of TRANSACT/RETRACT operations.\nAfter each operation, verify all previously-observed datoms remain present.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ S ∈ Store, S' = TRANSACT(S, T) for any T: S ⊆ S' (monotonicity: once asserted, never lost) ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :spec/falsification :v "Any operation that reduces `store.datoms.len()` or removes a previously-observed datom from the set." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4 Axiom 2, C1, ADRS FD-001" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "e28e7edc1de3fd309bdb24646b12535d322634aa0f3488861155aaade266b8c3" :a :spec/verification :v "`V:TYPE`, `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-002 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :db/doc :v "Strict Transaction Growth" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4, ADRS PO-001\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ S, T: |TRANSACT(S, T)| > |S|\n  (every transaction adds at least its tx_entity metadata datoms)\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nFor all transitions S →[TRANSACT(T)] S':\n  `|S'.datoms| > |S.datoms|`\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n#[kani::ensures(|result| old(store.len()) < store.len())]\nfn transact(store: &mut Store, tx: Transaction<Committed>) -> Result<TxReceipt, TxApplyError>;\n```\n\n**Falsification**: A TRANSACT operation that leaves the store size unchanged.\n\n**proptest strategy**: After every transact, assert `store.len() > pre_len`.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ S, T: |TRANSACT(S, T)| > |S| (every transaction adds at least its tx_entity metadata datoms) ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :spec/falsification :v "A TRANSACT operation that leaves the store size unchanged." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4, ADRS PO-001" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "215a0770d916ac1eafe42cc79e2720ce1313878eb185475a3845b18ff65c7723" :a :spec/verification :v "`V:PROP`, `V:KANI`" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-003 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :db/doc :v "Content-Addressable Identity" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4 Axiom 1, C2, ADRS FD-007\n**Verification**: `V:TYPE`, `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ d₁, d₂ ∈ D:\n  (d₁.e, d₁.a, d₁.v, d₁.tx, d₁.op) = (d₂.e, d₂.a, d₂.v, d₂.tx, d₂.op)\n  ⟺ d₁ = d₂\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nFor all reachable states S:\n  No two distinct datoms in `S.datoms` have identical five-tuple values.\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n// Enforced by BTreeSet/HashSet with (e, a, v, tx, op) as the key.\n// Two insertions of the same five-tuple result in one stored datom.\nimpl Hash for Datom { /* hash all five fields */ }\nimpl Eq for Datom { /* compare all five fields */ }\n```\n\n**Falsification**: Two datoms with identical `(e, a, v, tx, op)` coexisting in the store\nas distinct entries. Or: two datoms with different `(e, a, v, tx, op)` comparing as equal.\n\n**proptest strategy**: Generate pairs of datoms with varying field equality. Verify Hash/Eq\nconsistency: equal datoms produce identical hashes; distinct datoms stored separately.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ d₁, d₂ ∈ D: (d₁.e, d₁.a, d₁.v, d₁.tx, d₁.op) = (d₂.e, d₂.a, d₂.v, d₂.tx, d₂.op) ⟺ d₁ = d₂ ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :spec/falsification :v "Two datoms with identical `(e, a, v, tx, op)` coexisting in the store as distinct entries. Or: two datoms with different `(e, a, v, tx, op)` comparing as equal." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4 Axiom 1, C2, ADRS FD-007" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bed990329010060fbee0d763448857bb4d3e63b624317673b4fbfff9b7098f31" :a :spec/verification :v "`V:TYPE`, `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-004 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :db/doc :v "CRDT Merge Commutativity" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4 Axiom 2, C4, ADRS AS-001, L1\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`, `V:MODEL`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ S₁, S₂ ∈ Store: MERGE(S₁, S₂) = MERGE(S₂, S₁)\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nFor all reachable store pairs (S₁, S₂):\n  `MERGE(S₁, S₂).datoms = MERGE(S₂, S₁).datoms`\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n#[kani::ensures(|_| merge(s1, s2).datoms == merge(s2, s1).datoms)]\nfn merge(s1: &Store, s2: &Store) -> Store;\n```\n\n**Falsification**: Any pair of stores where `MERGE(S₁, S₂) ≠ MERGE(S₂, S₁)`.\n\n**proptest strategy**: Generate two random stores, merge in both orders, assert identical\ndatom sets. Run 100,000+ iterations with varying store sizes.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ S₁, S₂ ∈ Store: MERGE(S₁, S₂) = MERGE(S₂, S₁) ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :spec/falsification :v "Any pair of stores where `MERGE(S₁, S₂) ≠ MERGE(S₂, S₁)`." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4 Axiom 2, C4, ADRS AS-001, L1" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "d36c99e195e7546e6286a27ab60957fa169d163f6013a6944bff68a16bfa6618" :a :spec/verification :v "`V:PROP`, `V:KANI`, `V:MODEL`" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-005 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :db/doc :v "CRDT Merge Associativity" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4, C4, ADRS AS-001, L2\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`, `V:MODEL`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ S₁, S₂, S₃ ∈ Store: MERGE(MERGE(S₁, S₂), S₃) = MERGE(S₁, MERGE(S₂, S₃))\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nFor all reachable store triples:\n  Merge order does not affect the final datom set.\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n#[kani::ensures(|_| merge(&merge(s1, s2), s3).datoms == merge(s1, &merge(s2, s3)).datoms)]\n```\n\n**Falsification**: Any triple of stores where regrouping merge operations produces different results.\n\n**proptest strategy**: Generate three random stores, merge in both groupings, assert equal.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ S₁, S₂, S₃ ∈ Store: MERGE(MERGE(S₁, S₂), S₃) = MERGE(S₁, MERGE(S₂, S₃)) ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :spec/falsification :v "Any triple of stores where regrouping merge operations produces different results." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4, C4, ADRS AS-001, L2" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "590d60c8b9720dd2743ccafd474571ebd89d10986e19d5c637046e2f3cd8bdf9" :a :spec/verification :v "`V:PROP`, `V:KANI`, `V:MODEL`" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-006 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :db/doc :v "CRDT Merge Idempotency" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4, C4, ADRS AS-001, PD-004, L3\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ S ∈ Store: MERGE(S, S) = S\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nMerging a store with itself produces no change.\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n#[kani::ensures(|_| merge(s, s).datoms == s.datoms)]\n```\n\n**Falsification**: A store where `MERGE(S, S)` differs from `S`.\n\n**proptest strategy**: Generate random store, merge with self, assert datom sets equal.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ S ∈ Store: MERGE(S, S) = S ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :spec/falsification :v "A store where `MERGE(S, S)` differs from `S`." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4, C4, ADRS AS-001, PD-004, L3" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "30fb92550dcbbb0cef8e6dce65e04d8f2cd235987b7c36ef5875974b12a002c7" :a :spec/verification :v "`V:PROP`, `V:KANI`" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :db/ident :v :spec/inv-store-007 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :spec/element-type :v :spec.element/invariant :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :spec/namespace :v :spec.ns/store :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :db/doc :v "CRDT Merge Monotonicity" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :spec/source-file :v "01-store.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4, C4, L4\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ S₁, S₂ ∈ Store: S₁ ⊆ MERGE(S₁, S₂) ∧ S₂ ⊆ MERGE(S₁, S₂)\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nMerging never loses datoms from either input.\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\n#[kani::ensures(|result| s1.datoms.is_subset(&result.datoms)\n                      && s2.datoms.is_subset(&result.datoms))]\n```\n\n**Falsification**: Any datom present in S₁ or S₂ but absent from `MERGE(S₁, S₂)`.\n\n**proptest strategy**: Generate two stores, merge, verify both inputs are subsets of result.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ S₁, S₂ ∈ Store: S₁ ⊆ MERGE(S₁, S₂) ∧ S₂ ⊆ MERGE(S₁, S₂) ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :spec/falsification :v "Any datom present in S₁ or S₂ but absent from `MERGE(S₁, S₂)`." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "cf788354b3b23f84f303181126449372707a2a9951ad4bb871664e1f6133bea1" :a :element/traces-to :v "SEED §4, C4, L4" :op :assert}
