   {:e #blake3 "1e6cdcb23d6b2611ceac3550471a6fe6f3ceb9528929ffcbc0ac90765c7d9739" :a :spec/source-file :v "02-schema.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "1e6cdcb23d6b2611ceac3550471a6fe6f3ceb9528929ffcbc0ac90765c7d9739" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: SEED §4, ADRS PO-001\n**Verification**: `V:TYPE`, `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 0\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\n∀ TRANSACT(S, T):\n  ∀ d ∈ T.datoms:\n    d.a ∈ schema(S)                              — attribute must exist\n    typeof(d.v) = schema(S).valueType(d.a)       — value type must match\n    (d.op = Retract ⟹ ∃ d' ∈ S: d'.e = d.e ∧ d'.a = d.a ∧ d'.op = Assert)\n      — can only retract what was asserted\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nNo datom with an undefined attribute or mistyped value enters the store.\nRetractions require a prior assertion of the same entity-attribute pair.\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\nimpl Transaction<Building> {\n    pub fn commit(self, schema: &Schema) -> Result<Transaction<Committed>, TxValidationError> {\n        for datom in &self.datoms {\n            let attr_def = schema.attribute(&datom.attribute)\n                .ok_or(TxValidationError::UnknownAttribute(datom.attribute.clone()))?;\n            attr_def.validate_value(&datom.value)?;\n        }\n        Ok(Transaction { _state: PhantomData::<Committed>, ..self })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Falsification**: A datom with attribute `:foo/bar` entering the store when no attribute\n`:foo/bar` is defined in the schema.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "1e6cdcb23d6b2611ceac3550471a6fe6f3ceb9528929ffcbc0ac90765c7d9739" :a :spec/statement :v "``` ∀ TRANSACT(S, T): ∀ d ∈ T.datoms: d.a ∈ schema(S)                              — attribute must exist typeof(d.v) = schema(S).valueType(d.a)       — value type must match (d.op = Retract ⟹ ∃ d' ∈ S: d'.e = d.e ∧ d'.a = d.a ∧ d'.op = Assert) — can only retract what was asserted ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "1e6cdcb23d6b2611ceac3550471a6fe6f3ceb9528929ffcbc0ac90765c7d9739" :a :spec/falsification :v "A datom with attribute `:foo/bar` entering the store when no attribute `:foo/bar` is defined in the schema." :op :assert}
