   {:e #blake3 "292a084b15c791149b75b5ed6b415ee04eaabeffa0c1dc88bc2d6cdc241c7573" :a :db/doc :v "Betweenness Centrality" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "292a084b15c791149b75b5ed6b415ee04eaabeffa0c1dc88bc2d6cdc241c7573" :a :spec/source-file :v "03-query.md" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "292a084b15c791149b75b5ed6b415ee04eaabeffa0c1dc88bc2d6cdc241c7573" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: ADRS SQ-004\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`\n**Stage**: 1\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\n```\nBetweenness centrality measures how often a vertex lies on shortest paths:\n\nBC(v) = Σ_{s≠v≠t} σ_st(v) / σ_st\n\nwhere σ_st = number of shortest paths from s to t,\n      σ_st(v) = number of those passing through v.\n\nProperties:\n  1. Range: BC(v) ∈ [0, (|V|-1)(|V|-2)/2] (unnormalized)\n  2. Normalized: BC_norm(v) = BC(v) / ((|V|-1)(|V|-2)/2) ∈ [0, 1]\n  3. Bottleneck identification: high BC ⟹ vertex is a critical dependency\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nBetweenness centrality is a Stratum 1 query. It identifies bottleneck\nentities in the dependency graph — entities whose removal would maximally\ndisrupt connectivity. Used by R(t) work routing (INV-GUIDANCE-010) to\nprioritize unblocking high-betweenness tasks.\n\n#### Level 2 (Implementation Contract)\n```rust\npub fn betweenness_centrality(\n    store: &Store,\n    entity_type: &Attribute,\n    dep_attr: &Attribute,\n    normalized: bool,\n) -> Vec<(EntityId, f64)> {\n    // Brandes' algorithm: O(V × E)\n    // Returns entities sorted by descending centrality\n}\n```\n\n**Falsification**: Normalized betweenness score falls outside [0, 1], OR\na vertex on every shortest path between two components has BC = 0.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "292a084b15c791149b75b5ed6b415ee04eaabeffa0c1dc88bc2d6cdc241c7573" :a :spec/statement :v "``` Betweenness centrality measures how often a vertex lies on shortest paths: BC(v) = Σ_{s≠v≠t} σ_st(v) / σ_st where σ_st = number of shortest paths from s to t, σ_st(v) = number of those passing through v. Properties: 1. Range: BC(v) ∈ [0, (|V|-1)(|V|-2)/2] (unnormalized) 2. Normalized: BC_norm(v) = BC(v) / ((|V|-1)(|V|-2)/2) ∈ [0, 1] 3. Bottleneck identification: high BC ⟹ vertex is a critical dependency ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "292a084b15c791149b75b5ed6b415ee04eaabeffa0c1dc88bc2d6cdc241c7573" :a :spec/falsification :v "Normalized betweenness score falls outside [0, 1], OR a vertex on every shortest path between two components has BC = 0." :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "292a084b15c791149b75b5ed6b415ee04eaabeffa0c1dc88bc2d6cdc241c7573" :a :element/traces-to :v "ADRS SQ-004" :op :assert}
