   {:e #blake3 "908591caed7cfac57c85ca0db7ae075682d78dc6d8c7b8abbeaa2002c0b8e084" :a :element/body :v "**Traces to**: ADRS IB-005\n**Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:KANI`\n**Stage**: 1\n\n#### Level 0 (Algebraic Law)\nThe Q(t) formula accounts for attention quality degradation:\n```\nQ(t) = k*_eff(t) × attention_decay(k*_eff(t))\n\nQ(t) degrades faster than k*_eff(t) when k*_eff < 0.6\n  because attention quality drops before context fills.\n```\n\n#### Level 1 (State Invariant)\nThe MEASURE transition computes Q(t) using the piecewise attention_decay function.\nOutput budget is derived from Q(t), not raw k*_eff.\n\n**Falsification**: Output budget is computed from raw k*_eff without applying\nthe attention_decay quality adjustment.\n\n---" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "908591caed7cfac57c85ca0db7ae075682d78dc6d8c7b8abbeaa2002c0b8e084" :a :spec/statement :v "The Q(t) formula accounts for attention quality degradation: ``` Q(t) = k*_eff(t) × attention_decay(k*_eff(t)) Q(t) degrades faster than k*_eff(t) when k*_eff < 0.6 because attention quality drops before context fills. ```" :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "908591caed7cfac57c85ca0db7ae075682d78dc6d8c7b8abbeaa2002c0b8e084" :a :spec/falsification :v "Output budget is computed from raw k*_eff without applying the attention_decay quality adjustment." :op :assert}
